## Mars

- 4 billion years ago : a planet that could have been another earth
  - ![mars-past-and-present](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/mars-past-and-present.png)
- today : cold and hostile
  - ![earth-vs-mars-stats](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/earth-vs-mars-stats.png)
- What happened ?
  - atmosphere : extremely important for heat conservation
    - ![atmosphere-earth](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/atmosphere-earth.png)
  - mars's atmosphere : blown away by solar wind
    - ![solar-wind-particles](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/solar-wind-particles.png)
    - gas particles physically sputtered away by high speed particles constituting the solar wind
- Earth's atmosphere : protected by its magnetic field
  - which deflects solar wind's charged particles
  - Earth's core : $$Fe$$ and $$Ni$$
    - dynamo effect
      - electromagnetic induction
        - ![magnetic-field-generation](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/magnetic-field-generation.png)
      - heat convection
        - ![dynamo-effect](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/dynamo-effect.gif)
      - Movement of outer core induced by Earth's rotation
        - ![earth-rotation-magnetic-induction](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/earth-rotation-magnetic-induction.gif)
  - weak spot : the poles
    - ![creeping-in](/home/rongzhou/Documents/ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/capture_26-12-2025-19-36-09.png)
    - solar wind particles creep in
    - cause of polar auroras !
    - ![polar auroras](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/Northern_Lights_timelapse.gif)
- Terraforming mars
  - super conducting ring : artifical magnetic field
    - ![super-conductor-ring](/home/rongzhou/Documents/ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/capture_26-12-2025-19-41-07.png)
    - superconducting : significantly less energy consumption
      - Space : $ T \longrightarrow 0K$
      - perfect for superconduction
    - strategically placed between Mars and Sun
      - Lagrange point : balanced gravitational pull
  - or a super conductor torus (belt) !
    - ![super conductor belt](../../../ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/superconductor-belt.png)
    - uses less material than the super conducting ring (suprisingly)
    - ![torus](/home/rongzhou/Documents/ronzz-img/public/img/brilliant-graphics/astronomy/capture_26-12-2025-19-51-49.png)
    - $$ V=2\pi R\cdot \pi r^2=2\pi ^2 R r^2 $$
    - for a superconductor ring : power correlated positively with $r$ and $R$
    - hence to avoid self-destruction $$ r \propto \frac{1}{R^2} $$
    - $$ V= 2\pi ^2 R \frac{k}{R^2}=\frac{2\pi ^2k}{R} \propto \frac{1}{R} $$
  - $$ \because R_{conducting\ belt} \gg R_{conducting ring} $$
  - $$ \therefore VR_{conducting\ belt} \gg V_{conducting ring} $$